<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,461,796]" pageId="12" pageNumber="45">
In tropical America, this species occurs from 
<collectingCountry box="[732,826,500,526]" name="Mexico" pageId="12" pageNumber="45">Mexico</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[870,994,500,526]" name="Argentina" pageId="12" pageNumber="45">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and is widely distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[1360,1436,500,526]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="45">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Govaerts, R. &amp; Sobral, M. &amp; Ashton, P. &amp; Barrie, F. &amp; Holst, B. K. &amp; Landrum, L. &amp; Matsumoto, K. &amp; Mazine, F. F. &amp; Lughadha, E. N. &amp; Proenca, C. &amp; Soares-Silva, L. H. &amp; Wilson, P. G. &amp; Lucas, E." box="[159,402,538,564]" pageId="12" pageNumber="45" refId="ref13244" refString="Govaerts, R., Sobral, M., Ashton, P., Barrie, F., Holst, B. K., Landrum, L., Matsumoto, K., Mazine, F. F., Lughadha, E. N., Proenca, C., Soares-Silva, L. H., Wilson, P. G. &amp; Lucas, E. (2010) World Checklist of Myrtaceae. The Board of Trustees of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew. Published on the Internet; http: // www. kew. org / wcsp /. Accessed: 29 July 2010." type="url" year="2010">
Govaerts 
<emphasis box="[274,332,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
